column5: Those shots were not that far away Rich. You maybe right.Bad flash. No more baiting.
I love those shots, thanks for posting them. Jim
Today Brian... the one big Tom had to go 25 to 30 lbs
Wow, makes me wanna seriously take the hunting and turkey courses.
If we put out some plywood with glue on it  and seeds we could just wait till a few get stuck and then go to Wayne's to grocery shop for thanksgiving
..and did I mention I didn't have to get out of my computer chair to take the picture and post it!
Awesome Wayne. Just got back from the field stand Look who visited this morning. The time is what makes the pic,s exciting.      I think she likes the buck urine I used to cover my scent.

That's a funny looking dog!!!  I love hunting season! All the idiots are off the lake and out in the woods shooting themselves and each other, falling out of their tree stands and breaking their necks and backs, or flipping their ATV's over on themselves.  .. and I have the whole lake to myself!!!
it's Bambi isn't it cute     Grandma  Grandpa just said he's going to shoot Bambi
Veal....
Right beside the mashed taters.
You fergot the gravy Bubba!!!.. nice brown gravy with mushrooms, onions.... and Collard Greens!!!
Good luck with your hunts Brian.  Hope you bag a fall gobbler and some venison for the freezer too.  Fall is here and hunting is just around the corner.  Can't wait!!
will ya let me get some fishin in before you get me started on the next thing.... smoked jerky..........  I'll take one veal please. A Turkey too.
Ahem....Where'd ya say that stand was again Richy  Bushart
How much cash do you have?

I just knew this stand was going to produce something. The daytime shots really have me pumped,as we all know, you cant hunt in the dark.LOL  First my feathered friends.I,ll be looking for one of them this fall.          Now the shots that count.LOL
Hey, that's neat B.  Never knew there was such thing as a trail cam until you started posting these.  Joey
All i see are eyes and deer with no heads.  Good luck with the hunt.

Nice pics Brian, but, will they still be there when you need them to be? It's amazing how when we scout out areas, and find lots of sign, when the time comes, NOTHING, ZERO, ZIP, NO ACTIVITY.  Hope that does not happen for you though, looking forward to a successful hunting report.
..and ta think I just have to look out my window ! lol

Misfish looks like an afternoon hunt for you...all the better. Those birds are obviously roosting close by, if they came in at that time of the day. I hunted a similar situation last fall.  Watch out for the fly down at dawn...scared the poop out of me. Good Luck with the deer. Wayne you obviously have a varmit problem that needs looked after:)
That is very cool!
these pictures are making me hungry
looks like you are going to be eating well this fall
I do Tom... but considering his success I"m always looking for new contractors!

It,s pretty cool thats forsure J.   Thanks Glen  Tom ,there is a soya bean plot,brocolli and corn this year to keep them around. I have not seen this much sign in all the years I have hunted this piece of property.   Wayne I wish I had the property you do. Would save on driving.LOL   Thanks Tree30eight This one spot has great potential.Im hopeing to take a small bird this fall.    Lets hope it,s not track soup this season.LOL   Hey,I,ll take care of the problem.
One Word MisMan  POW!!!!!!!  Bushart
OOOHHHH!!!!!!!!!!!!!    BURRRNNNN,
What are friends for Tom.
Maybe I can tie a string to one of their legs... so they're around when you get here Brian!    Hell maybe I'd better tie up two and you can bring the other contractor Remo....
Look like samsquatch eyes to me.
nice shots misfish  my new friend visited me last night
Awesome Brian Good action at the cam  When is your season opener for them birds?? Jacques

Nice pics. I've had one of these cam's for a couple year's now and it has been a great tool for hunting and trapping. I just recently set it up and I've allready got some good action, but I think the best is still to come.  Here's a young buck   A doe and two fauns   A little spike horn   And this big guy has been around all summer long, I knew he'd appear eventually. Bu t I'm not sure if the is two different moose??     In two weeks I shot 345 pictures. Most of them being the same two bucks, and the doe with 2 fauns. and of course old bullwinkle.
lucG it looks like they are still in velvet? Nice picture all.   Art

The fall season opens on the 13th of October and carries for 2 weeks. One bird of either sex.   Great shots there guys. I put my cam back out on the field stand.I think I had it too high the last time.  Next year I,ll be upgrading the cam,as the flash on this one sux.  4 more sleeps.

The flash is only good for like 30 feet, not yards . The pics of the deer you have they look like they are quite a distance away. My cam is the same one and the flash is very bright on a deer that is 10 feet away from the cam. Your deer are so far away they look like mice. Get them closer and then see what the pics look like. Use a pile of salt or something.
